  <discussion>The name Amaranthus torreyi has been widely misapplied to at least two other
        species, 7. A. arenicola and 6. A. watsonii. Because of that, the name A. bigelovii was used
        for A. torreyi by J. D. Sauer (1955) and in some recent floras. Sometimes A. torreyi
        (California and Arizona) and A. bigelovii (New Mexico and Texas) are recognized as separate
        species. The nomenclature and taxonomic relationships in this group should be critically
        reviewed based on type specimens and additional experimental and field studies.</discussion>
